{"questionId":"26541","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The region bounded by&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;and the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis is rotated through <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mi>π</mi></math>&nbsp;about the <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>-axis to form a solid.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the volume of the solid formed. Give your answer in the form&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mi>c</mi></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>, where&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>∈</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">ℤ</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>volume&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><msubsup><mfenced open=\"[\" close=\"]\"><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>x</mi></mrow></mfenced><mn>0</mn><mn>2</mn></msubsup></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mn>4</mn></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mn>4</mn></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>use of log laws seen, for example&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>4</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mfenced><mrow><mfrac><mn>9</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mfenced><mfrac><mn>4</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">π</mi><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mfenced><mrow><mn>9</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mo> </mo><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong><br>Note:</strong> Other correct integer solutions are possible and should be accepted for&nbsp;example&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>c</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>4</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"26541","referenceCode":"22M.1.AHL.TZ1.14b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the volume of the solid formed. Give your answer in the form π4a+b lnc, where a, b, c∈ℤ.","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.12—Areas under a curve onto x or y axis. Volumes of revolution about x and y"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}